[quest]Strange Matter Aggregator[/quest]

§6Machine Type:§r Modularized Machine - §aStrange Matter Aggregator§r

You must set the number of rings per multi-specific block within the Machine UI.

Multi-Specific Blocks: 

Oscillator
Constraintor
Merger

[warn]DO NOT, AND I REPEAT DO NOT USE MORE THAN §91§r HOLOGRAM PROJECTOR ON THIS MULTI[/warn]

[note]It is recommended to go for 15 15 24 for Rings. The Multi will be about 1100 blocks long[/note]

Input Hatch of SpaceTime Maintenance Fluid: §1§aLeft of the Controller Block§r
Input Bus of Core Element and Annihilation Constrainer: §1§aRight of the Controller Block§r

[note]Higher Tier, more rings, more benefits, but more resources required[/note]

Place §9Modular Hatches§r around the controller to enhance your machine.

§6Installable Modules§r are: 

§cPower Consumption Controller Module§r: Reduces machine energy consumption
§cSpeed Controller Module§r: Increases machine processing speed

§9 -------§r §6SpaceTime Oscillator§r §9------- §r

§3Base Run Time§r: Higher the tier, the shorter the run time
§3Basic Materials Consumption§r: Higher number of rings, lower amount of basic materials  consumed
§3SpaceTime Maintenance Fluid Consumption§r: More Rings, More Fluid consumed
§3Core Element and Annihilation Constrainer Consumption§r: Higher Tier & More Rings, lower consumption rate

§9 -------§r §6SpaceTime Constraintor§r §9------- §r

§3Consumption Rate of Auxiliary Materials§r: Higher the level, the lower the consumption rate
§3Actual Running Time§r: Higher the tier, the longer the running time is
§3SpaceTime Maintenance Fluid Consumption§r: More rings, less fluid consumed

§9 -------§r §6SpaceTime Merger§r §9------- §r

§3Maximum Continuous Running Points§r: Higher the tier, higher the §aContinuous Running Points§r limit
§3Byproduct Outputs§r: More rings, the more outputs
§3Power Consumption§r: Higher tier, more rings, the higher the power consumption

§9 -------§r §3SpaceTime Maintenance Fluid§r §9------- §r

Set which SpaceTime Maintenance Fluid Tier within the Machine UI:

§9T1§r: §c576L§r Molten SpaceTime
§9T2§r: §c96L§r Molten Universium
§9T3§r: §c16L§r Molten Magnetohydrodynamically Constrained Star Matter

Using Advanced SpaceTime Maintenance Fluid increases number of fuel rods crafted per Annihilation Constrainer and Core Element, and reduces the consumption of Fluid and Auxiliary Materials. 

The type of byproducts depends on the SpaceTime Maintenance Fluid used:

§9T1§r: Molten Infinity and Molten Hypogen
§9T2§r: Molten SpaceTime and Molten Shirabon
§9T3§r: Molten Universium

§6 ------------- §r

§1Continous Operation§r will produce byproducts and more of the main output

For each successful run, §3Continuous Running Points§r is increased by one.

You must provide sufficient SpaceTime Maintenance Fluid to maintain continuous operation

Provide §aCore Elements§r to obtain T2 Products

If you input core elements, it will output the T2 Strange Annihilation Fuel Rod instead | Byproduct yields are doubled
